1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,753
- [OLSEN GROANING]
<i>- Bro, are you okay?</i>

2
00:00:03,837 --> 00:00:05,338
<i>- Stay over there!</i>
- [GRETA YELPS]

3
00:00:05,922 --> 00:00:07,048
<i>Olsen!</i>

4
00:00:07,132 --> 00:00:09,134
<i>Emil is still alive. He's here.</i>

5
00:00:09,217 --> 00:00:10,969
<i>He wants revenge</i>

6
00:00:11,052 --> 00:00:13,221
<i>because I had an affair with his daughter.</i>

7
00:00:13,304 --> 00:00:17,517
<i>And now she's missing, and Emil thinks</i>
<i>I know where she is, but I don't.</i>

8
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:18,643
<i>I don't know.</i>

9
00:00:19,310 --> 00:00:21,479
[DADO] <i>Don't try to remove that.</i>

10
00:00:21,563 --> 00:00:24,774
<i>I'm the only one who can remove it.</i>

11
00:00:24,858 --> 00:00:28,028
<i>If you get more than 50 meters away,</i>
<i>this is what will happen to you.</i>

12
00:00:28,111 --> 00:00:31,156
<i>- The bombs will detonate automatically.</i>
- [EXPLOSION ECHOING]

13
00:00:31,239 --> 00:00:32,991
[OFFICER] <i>Hurry up, keep running!</i>

14
00:00:33,074 --> 00:00:34,492
<i>Abort mission.</i>

15
00:00:34,576 --> 00:00:36,703
<i>Withdraw and exit</i>
<i>the hospital immediately.</i>

16
00:00:37,287 --> 00:00:38,496
<i>What happened?</i>

17
00:00:38,580 --> 00:00:42,125
[EMIL] <i>Bring Captain Jacinto to me.</i>

18
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:44,169
- [GROANS]
- [EMIL]<i> We have something to discuss.</i>

19
00:00:44,252 --> 00:00:48,590
<i>We need more hostages.</i>

20
00:00:48,673 --> 00:00:49,799
<i>Don't worry.</i>

21
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:52,177
<i>It's safe downstairs.</i>
<i>The cops were pulled out.</i>

22
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:54,512
<i>That was the agreement I made</i>
<i>with the general.</i>

23
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:07,192
[GASPS] Who…

24
00:01:07,275 --> 00:01:08,818
Who are you?

25
00:01:10,653 --> 00:01:12,530
Where's Papa?

26
00:01:13,198 --> 00:01:14,699
Bring me to him.

27
00:01:14,783 --> 00:01:17,368
No, you must stay here.

28
00:01:17,452 --> 00:01:19,579
Your father asked us to protect you.

29
00:01:20,997 --> 00:01:24,292
Look, you shouldn't have come back here.

30
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:28,171
Your father made sure you were sent
to the hospital to be treated,

31
00:01:28,254 --> 00:01:32,217
but he knows once you recover,
you'll go straight to jail.

32
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:37,263
That's why we tried to get you out
before we attacked, to ensure your safety,

33
00:01:37,347 --> 00:01:40,350
but you're just so stubborn.

34
00:01:40,433 --> 00:01:41,851
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

35
00:01:41,935 --> 00:01:43,978
I'm Homer, a friend of your father.

36
00:01:44,062 --> 00:01:45,563
Lucas is my brother.

37
00:01:45,647 --> 00:01:48,441
We owe Boss Emil a lot,
so we won't abandon you.

38
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:54,697
If you really want to repay Papa,

39
00:01:54,781 --> 00:01:56,241
then stop him.

40
00:01:58,118 --> 00:01:59,035
Listen.

41
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:03,915
Just trust your father.
He won't let you and your sister down.

42
00:02:03,998 --> 00:02:10,046
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

43
00:02:22,517 --> 00:02:24,310
What's the patient's name?

44
00:02:24,394 --> 00:02:26,855
How long have they been confined here?

45
00:02:26,938 --> 00:02:30,650
[GWEN] It's only been a few days, Doc.
Her name is Marie Santos.

46
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:34,112
I wanted to get her out
when the commotion started,

47
00:02:34,195 --> 00:02:35,947
but I got scared.

48
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:37,699
Plus, she's not strong enough to move.

49
00:02:38,825 --> 00:02:40,451
What happened to her?

50
00:02:40,535 --> 00:02:41,911
She just got out of surgery.

51
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:44,164
[IVAN] For what?

52
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:46,875
Let's just hurry, Doc.

53
00:02:46,958 --> 00:02:49,043
Thank goodness you're here.

54
00:02:51,337 --> 00:02:57,594
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

55
00:03:07,186 --> 00:03:13,109
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

56
00:03:44,849 --> 00:03:47,977
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

57
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:49,771
[CUTTER CRANKS]

58
00:03:58,780 --> 00:04:00,823
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

59
00:04:08,748 --> 00:04:10,500
What's the situation inside?

60
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:12,961
We were able to tap into
the security cameras earlier,

61
00:04:13,044 --> 00:04:14,045
but we lost the feed.

62
00:04:14,128 --> 00:04:19,926
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

63
00:04:29,978 --> 00:04:31,062
[PHONE BEEPS]

64
00:04:32,063 --> 00:04:34,524
- [INHALES DEEPLY]
- [LINE RINGS]

65
00:04:34,607 --> 00:04:36,901
I cut the CCTV connection, Boss Emil.

66
00:04:37,652 --> 00:04:40,029
I've done what you asked.
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

67
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:42,282
Maybe you can tell Lucas--

68
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:45,868
Listen, okay? We aren't done yet.

69
00:04:50,373 --> 00:04:55,962
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

70
00:05:12,895 --> 00:05:18,818
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

71
00:05:30,246 --> 00:05:31,831
Based on the last CCTV footage,

72
00:05:31,914 --> 00:05:34,876
Emil Padua and his accomplices
are still on the rooftop

73
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:36,919
with the hostages.

74
00:05:37,003 --> 00:05:40,339
The hospital security team said
they can't verify

75
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:43,092
if there are any more civilians
left inside.

76
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:44,969
The building has been almost evacuated.

77
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:47,513
"Almost"? They aren't sure?

78
00:05:48,181 --> 00:05:49,724
As well as Emil Padua's daughter,

79
00:05:49,807 --> 00:05:52,560
there's Captain Jacinto,
and the cops assigned to watch him.

80
00:05:52,643 --> 00:05:54,520
The hospital security team can't verify

81
00:05:54,604 --> 00:05:56,522
if there are any more civilians
left inside, sir.

82
00:05:56,606 --> 00:06:00,902
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

83
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:10,036
[ICE BREATHING HEAVILY]

84
00:06:10,119 --> 00:06:10,953
[DOOR CLOSES]

85
00:06:11,037 --> 00:06:12,789
[JOY CRYING, WHIMPERING]

86
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:14,916
It hurts. It hurts so much.

87
00:06:14,999 --> 00:06:16,959
- [CRIES]
- I know it hurts.

88
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:19,378
But be strong.

89
00:06:19,462 --> 00:06:25,051
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

90
00:06:25,134 --> 00:06:26,427
- [KNOCKING]
- [WHIMPERS]

91
00:06:26,511 --> 00:06:27,512
[ICE] I got it.

92
00:06:27,595 --> 00:06:30,473
[JOY CRYING]

93
00:06:30,556 --> 00:06:32,683
[HAPPY] Joy…

94
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:36,270
Listen. Take a deep breath.

95
00:06:38,189 --> 00:06:41,067
[JOY WHIMPERS, CRIES]

96
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:44,153
[JOY GROANS]

97
00:06:46,030 --> 00:06:47,865
[WHIMPERS]

98
00:06:47,949 --> 00:06:49,534
I don't want that. Don't do it.

99
00:06:49,617 --> 00:06:51,619
We need to clean your wound.

100
00:06:51,702 --> 00:06:54,956
[JOY WHIMPERING]

101
00:07:04,048 --> 00:07:05,049
You can do it.

102
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:07,552
[JOY CRYING]

103
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:10,805
[WHIMPERS]

104
00:07:14,183 --> 00:07:16,477
- Hand me that.
- The gauze?

105
00:07:16,561 --> 00:07:18,062
Wait. Here, here, here.

106
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:20,481
Give me that.

107
00:07:21,774 --> 00:07:23,401
[MOUTHS SILENTLY]

108
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:30,241
[BOMB TICKING]

109
00:07:30,324 --> 00:07:32,326
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC STING]

110
00:07:34,662 --> 00:07:36,122
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

111
00:07:36,205 --> 00:07:37,874
[WHISPERS] There's a bomb.

112
00:07:37,957 --> 00:07:39,083
What?

113
00:07:40,209 --> 00:07:42,044
They planted bombs again?

114
00:07:42,128 --> 00:07:43,671
[MINNIE BREATHING HEAVILY]

115
00:07:43,754 --> 00:07:45,339
They're here again?

116
00:07:45,423 --> 00:07:47,008
[MIKE EXHALES DEEPLY]

117
00:07:47,091 --> 00:07:51,137
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

118
00:07:53,806 --> 00:07:55,183
[MINNIE EXHALES SHARPLY]

119
00:07:55,266 --> 00:07:57,685
[BOMBS TICKING]

120
00:07:57,768 --> 00:08:00,188
Where do we go now?

121
00:08:00,271 --> 00:08:02,315
Come. Let's go this way.

122
00:08:02,398 --> 00:08:03,816
Come here. This way.

123
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:05,026
Come here.

124
00:08:05,109 --> 00:08:07,320
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

125
00:08:10,615 --> 00:08:12,533
- [EXHALES SHARPLY]
- [MINNIE] What is it?

126
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:14,327
There's a dead man.

127
00:08:15,036 --> 00:08:16,204
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

128
00:08:16,287 --> 00:08:17,663
Cover…

129
00:08:17,747 --> 00:08:19,415
Cover your eyes, baby.

130
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:21,250
Come on. Let's go.

131
00:08:23,753 --> 00:08:24,754
[MINNIE BREATHES SHAKILY]

132
00:08:24,837 --> 00:08:26,130
- [MADDIE WHIMPERS]
- [MINNIE] Dear…

133
00:08:26,214 --> 00:08:27,590
Come on.

134
00:08:27,673 --> 00:08:29,342
- Mommy…
- Don't look.

135
00:08:29,425 --> 00:08:32,470
- Mommy…
- Don't look. Don't.

136
00:08:32,553 --> 00:08:34,680
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

137
00:08:34,764 --> 00:08:35,806
Hey!

138
00:08:36,516 --> 00:08:37,850
- Run!
- [MINNIE] No!

139
00:08:37,934 --> 00:08:39,227
- [ROMAN] Freeze!
- [MINNIE SCREAMS]

140
00:08:39,310 --> 00:08:41,646
[MINNIE CRYING]

141
00:08:42,271 --> 00:08:44,273
- [MIKE] Sir, no. Please.
- [ROMAN] Where are you going?!

142
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:46,067
- We have a child, sir.
- [ROMAN] Answer me!

143
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:48,945
- We have a child. Please--
- [ROMAN] I don't care!

144
00:08:49,028 --> 00:08:50,821
- Go over there!
- [MINNIE] Yes, sir.

145
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:51,989
We'll go with you.

146
00:08:52,073 --> 00:08:53,199
Okay.

147
00:08:56,244 --> 00:08:57,912
[IVAN] This is a bullet wound.

148
00:08:57,995 --> 00:08:59,288
How did she get this?

149
00:08:59,956 --> 00:09:02,124
Uh, she was in an accident, Doc.

150
00:09:04,126 --> 00:09:06,379
But I don't know the full details.

151
00:09:09,257 --> 00:09:11,425
Her wound is infected again.

152
00:09:11,926 --> 00:09:13,469
I have to clean it again.

153
00:09:14,428 --> 00:09:16,222
We will continue with the treatment.

154
00:09:18,474 --> 00:09:20,560
If that's the case, Doc,
I'll leave her to your care.

155
00:09:22,812 --> 00:09:27,608
I have to review the antibiotics
and IV that were given to her.

156
00:09:32,488 --> 00:09:34,240
Why is the name written here different?

157
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:37,493
"Gregorio Valdez"?

158
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:41,455
Sorry, Doc.
You're aware of the situation right now.

159
00:09:41,539 --> 00:09:43,165
There's a hostage situation.

160
00:09:43,249 --> 00:09:47,962
The nurse earlier was probably in shock
and gave me the wrong chart.

161
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:51,674
I need to review her chart.

162
00:09:51,757 --> 00:09:54,093
I'll check the hospital records.

163
00:09:58,889 --> 00:10:00,600
Just treat her.

164
00:10:00,683 --> 00:10:06,063
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:18,117
[BOMBS TICKING]

166
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:25,041
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

167
00:10:31,505 --> 00:10:32,715
[BEEPS]

168
00:10:38,846 --> 00:10:44,185
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

169
00:10:44,268 --> 00:10:45,561
[DADO CHUCKLES]

170
00:10:46,437 --> 00:10:47,647
Boss Emil.

171
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:49,065
The building is secured.

172
00:10:51,359 --> 00:10:53,235
Sir, without the CCTV feed,

173
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:56,364
we won't be able to know
what's happening in there.

174
00:10:56,447 --> 00:10:57,865
You're right.

175
00:10:57,948 --> 00:10:59,950
But if there's no CCTV,

176
00:11:00,034 --> 00:11:02,495
Emil Padua won't know
what we're doing either.

177
00:11:03,621 --> 00:11:08,376
[PHONE RINGING]

178
00:11:09,543 --> 00:11:10,586
Hello?

179
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:12,880
Who's this?

180
00:11:12,963 --> 00:11:16,509
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

181
00:11:16,592 --> 00:11:17,426
Emil?

182
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:20,554
Thank you for being obedient,
General Cabral.

183
00:11:20,638 --> 00:11:23,974
Are you sure all your men
left the building?

184
00:11:24,058 --> 00:11:25,267
Yes, I'm sure.

185
00:11:25,351 --> 00:11:26,394
Good.

186
00:11:26,477 --> 00:11:29,105
Because no one's allowed
to enter or exit anymore.

187
00:11:30,022 --> 00:11:32,608
There are bombs planted

188
00:11:32,691 --> 00:11:34,985
at all the entrances
and exits of the hospital.

189
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:36,821
If someone tries to pass through,

190
00:11:37,738 --> 00:11:38,906
boom!

191
00:11:39,573 --> 00:11:40,658
Emil.

192
00:11:41,659 --> 00:11:43,536
No one needs to get harmed, okay?

193
00:11:43,619 --> 00:11:45,496
That depends on you.

194
00:11:47,498 --> 00:11:50,543
All the CCTV cameras here in
the hospital are disabled now.

195
00:11:50,626 --> 00:11:54,797
But remember, I have eyes here inside.

196
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:56,215
Tell me.

197
00:11:57,550 --> 00:11:58,801
What do you really need?

198
00:11:59,427 --> 00:12:01,470
Just wait for my next order.

199
00:12:02,304 --> 00:12:04,598
Listen to what I say,
because if you don't,

200
00:12:06,058 --> 00:12:08,310
I'll kill one of the hostages.

201
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,524
[PHONE BEEPS]

202
00:12:21,907 --> 00:12:27,246
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

203
00:12:27,329 --> 00:12:29,498
[REPORTER] Sir, who were you talking to?

204
00:12:44,972 --> 00:12:50,019
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

205
00:12:51,228 --> 00:12:53,856
I can't shoot him
without someone hearing it.

206
00:12:55,483 --> 00:12:56,442
I know what to do.

207
00:12:56,525 --> 00:12:57,485
No, Wendy.

208
00:12:58,903 --> 00:13:01,447
[WENDY BREATHING HEAVILY]

209
00:13:01,530 --> 00:13:03,491
- [GASPS LOUDLY]
- [SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING]

210
00:13:04,366 --> 00:13:05,326
Hey!

211
00:13:06,118 --> 00:13:07,620
[WENDY] No, please.

212
00:13:07,703 --> 00:13:09,705
Please don't kill me!

213
00:13:09,788 --> 00:13:12,625
- What are you doing here?
- I'm just looking for my son.

214
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:13,667
Are you sure?

215
00:13:14,543 --> 00:13:16,253
- I'm begging you--
- Stay right there!

216
00:13:16,921 --> 00:13:18,631
Don't move! Come here!

217
00:13:20,132 --> 00:13:21,217
[WENDY WHIMPERS]

218
00:13:22,301 --> 00:13:23,719
[GRUNTS, GROANS]

219
00:13:25,304 --> 00:13:27,264
- [GROANS]
- Come on!

220
00:13:28,307 --> 00:13:30,601
Go on, Wendy. I'll handle this. Go.

221
00:13:32,436 --> 00:13:34,355
- [SCREAMS]
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC SWELLS]

222
00:13:34,438 --> 00:13:36,273
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [FREDO GRUNTS]

223
00:13:37,691 --> 00:13:39,860
[GUNSHOTS]

224
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:44,114
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

225
00:13:44,198 --> 00:13:51,080
[GRUNTING, GROANING]

226
00:13:57,586 --> 00:13:58,712
Go ahead!

227
00:13:58,796 --> 00:14:01,298
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

228
00:14:01,382 --> 00:14:02,466
[MAGNUS GRUNTS]

229
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:05,177
[GRUNTING]

230
00:14:05,261 --> 00:14:07,930
[MAGNUS COUGHS]

231
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:10,766
[GROANS]

232
00:14:10,849 --> 00:14:12,810
Wendy.
[COUGHS]

233
00:14:12,893 --> 00:14:18,566
[TENSE MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

234
00:14:21,819 --> 00:14:24,572
General Cabral said we should
find a change of clothes.

235
00:14:24,655 --> 00:14:26,323
We can't wear our uniforms.

236
00:14:27,741 --> 00:14:29,910
We'll pretend to be civilians?

237
00:14:30,494 --> 00:14:32,830
He said we need to
keep an eye on the place.

238
00:14:32,913 --> 00:14:33,914
What about this guy?

239
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:36,542
He won't be able to leave anyway.

240
00:14:36,625 --> 00:14:37,501
Let's go.

241
00:14:41,297 --> 00:14:44,300
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

242
00:14:44,383 --> 00:14:46,802
I thought there were no cops
left in the building.

243
00:14:48,304 --> 00:14:51,015
Go ahead. Shoot me.

244
00:14:51,724 --> 00:14:54,351
Hasn't your boss told you?

245
00:14:54,935 --> 00:14:56,687
We'll blow up the hostages.

246
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:01,317
Don't pull out your gun. Key.

247
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:06,488
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

248
00:15:06,572 --> 00:15:08,908
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [GRUNTING]

249
00:15:13,704 --> 00:15:14,830
[GUNSHOTS]

250
00:15:26,592 --> 00:15:31,889
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

251
00:15:31,972 --> 00:15:33,098
Get up!

252
00:15:33,682 --> 00:15:34,683
Get up.

253
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:39,855
[JACINTO GRUNTS]

254
00:15:47,363 --> 00:15:53,118
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

255
00:16:07,716 --> 00:16:08,717
Keep walking.

256
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:15,349
Go in. Go in!

257
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:23,273
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

258
00:16:24,274 --> 00:16:25,901
Hurry up!

259
00:16:26,402 --> 00:16:27,653
Olsen?

260
00:16:27,736 --> 00:16:28,779
Son!

261
00:16:28,862 --> 00:16:29,863
Olsen?

262
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:31,949
- Olsen, son!
- [OLSEN GROANS] Ma.

263
00:16:32,032 --> 00:16:33,492
- Magnus!
- Pa!

264
00:16:33,575 --> 00:16:35,035
[MAGNUS GRUNTS]

265
00:16:35,119 --> 00:16:36,578
[WENDY BREATHES SHAKILY]

266
00:16:37,329 --> 00:16:39,873
You'll pay for everything you've done!

267
00:16:39,957 --> 00:16:44,461
Good for you.
Your family is all together.

268
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:47,464
But it's okay.

269
00:16:47,965 --> 00:16:50,634
Soon, all of my family
will be together too.

270
00:16:50,718 --> 00:16:56,890
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

271
00:16:57,933 --> 00:16:58,934
[GOON] Go in!

272
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:01,270
Go in! Hurry up!

273
00:17:02,563 --> 00:17:05,691
Boss Emil, I brought you a gift.

274
00:17:12,406 --> 00:17:18,996
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

275
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:21,498
You'll be useful to me.

276
00:17:24,835 --> 00:17:25,878
And you?

277
00:17:28,714 --> 00:17:31,008
You might be useful to me too.

278
00:17:33,093 --> 00:17:36,138
Don't strap bombs on them yet.

279
00:17:36,764 --> 00:17:40,934
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

280
00:17:41,018 --> 00:17:43,479
Go sit there!

281
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:44,980
Hurry up!

282
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:49,276
You guys explain to Mr. Roja
what those are for.

283
00:17:49,359 --> 00:17:51,320
Leave them out of this!

284
00:17:52,071 --> 00:17:53,697
I'm the one you want, right?

285
00:17:53,781 --> 00:17:54,615
Right?

286
00:17:54,698 --> 00:17:56,366
Come on!

287
00:17:56,450 --> 00:17:59,161
Let's settle this once and for all!
Just the two of us!

288
00:18:00,287 --> 00:18:02,414
Relax, Mr. Roja.

289
00:18:03,957 --> 00:18:05,793
We'll get there.

290
00:18:05,876 --> 00:18:12,591
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

291
00:18:19,556 --> 00:18:20,641
[HOMER] Open it.

292
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:26,355
Where's the pharmacy?

293
00:18:29,024 --> 00:18:29,983
Where is it?!

294
00:18:30,067 --> 00:18:31,485
This way. Follow me.

295
00:18:31,568 --> 00:18:33,278
- Relax.
- Don't tell me what to do.

296
00:18:33,362 --> 00:18:34,488
Hurry up!

297
00:18:37,324 --> 00:18:44,164
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

298
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:59,972
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC SWELLS]

299
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:09,064
<i>Why did you say earlier</i>
<i>that we might be brothers?</i>

300
00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:11,859
<i>Isn't it better if we all know the truth?</i>

301
00:19:11,942 --> 00:19:14,903
<i>Your mother and my husband had an affair.</i>

302
00:19:16,446 --> 00:19:18,157
[HOMER] <i>Get the meds needed. Go!</i>

303
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:19,575
[GRUNTING]

304
00:19:19,658 --> 00:19:21,160
- [GUNSHOT]
- [GRUNTS]

305
00:19:22,536 --> 00:19:23,829
[MILA] <i>Get out of there.</i>

306
00:19:23,912 --> 00:19:25,998
<i>If you want me to get out of here alive,</i>

307
00:19:26,081 --> 00:19:27,207
<i>you'll help us.</i>

308
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:29,501
[REPORTER] <i>The hostage takers</i>
<i>have Liam Roja.</i>

309
00:19:29,585 --> 00:19:30,919
<i>You know, I don't care--</i>

310
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:32,838
<i>What did you say? You don't care?</i>

311
00:19:32,921 --> 00:19:35,924
<i>- We're going to abandon them?</i>
- [JOY] <i>We don't have a choice.</i>

312
00:19:36,008 --> 00:19:41,513
<i>Which one of you wants to show off</i>
<i>to those stubborn cops below?</i>

313
00:19:41,597 --> 00:19:42,556
<i>Padua, calm down.</i>

314
00:19:42,639 --> 00:19:45,017
<i>I don't think you believe me,</i>

315
00:19:45,893 --> 00:19:47,561
<i>so I'll give you a demonstration.</i>

316
00:19:48,312 --> 00:19:49,605
<i>Padua. Padua, wait.</i>

317
00:19:49,688 --> 00:19:52,399
<i>Just look up to the sky, General Cabral.</i>

318
00:19:53,150 --> 00:19:56,528
<i>One of you will have to fall from heaven</i>

319
00:19:56,612 --> 00:19:58,739
<i>and go to hell!</i>
